# Backend — tRPC, Database & API Patterns

## tRPC Router Pattern
```ts
// apps/web/src/server/trpc/routers/example.ts
import { z } from "zod";
import { protectedProcedure, createTRPCRouter } from "../init";

export const exampleRouter = createTRPCRouter({
  list: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.object({ limit: z.number().min(1).max(100).default(20) }))
    .query(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      // ctx.user is the authenticated Supabase user
      return db.select().from(table).where(eq(table.userId, ctx.user.id)).limit(input.limit);
    }),
});
```

- ALL procedures: Zod input validation, no exceptions
- Use `protectedProcedure` for any user-specific data
- One router file per domain — register in `_app.ts`

## Next.js API Route Pattern
```ts
// apps/web/src/app/api/[feature]/route.ts
export const maxDuration = 300; // long-running jobs only

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { user, error } = await getAuthUser(req);
  if (error || !user) return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });

  // IMPORTANT: always verify ownership before LLM calls
  const body = await req.json();
  // validate, check ownership, then proceed
}
```

## Drizzle Schema Conventions
```ts
// packages/db/src/schema/example.ts
import { pgTable, uuid, text, timestamp } from "drizzle-orm/pg-core";

export const examples = pgTable("examples", {
  id: uuid("id").primaryKey().defaultRandom(),
  userId: uuid("user_id").notNull(),
  content: text("content").notNull(),
  createdAt: timestamp("created_at", { withTimezone: true }).defaultNow().notNull(),
});

export type Example = typeof examples.$inferSelect;
export type NewExample = typeof examples.$inferInsert;
```

- `created_at timestamptz` is REQUIRED on every table
- Export both `$inferSelect` and `$inferInsert` types
- RLS policies: `supabase migration new <name>` → raw SQL only, never in Drizzle

## pgvector
- Embedding dimension: 1536 (text-embedding-3-small)
- Cosine similarity for concept dedup threshold: ≥ 0.92
- Column type: `vector(1536)` via `pgvector` extension

## Auth Pattern
```ts
import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server";

const supabase = createClient();
const { data: { user } } = await supabase.auth.getUser();
if (!user) redirect("/auth/login");
```
